I have been programming my self-positioning, but for some reason I get the startCompetition() error and I don’t know why. I checked it, but even my team’s programmer couldn’t help me. The error pops up when I press the auto-positioning button. When I click on it in the driver station, the robot code turns red. If I don’t click on it, my swerve movement works fine, but when I click on auto-positioning, I get the startCompetition error. Could someone help me figure out what’s going on? I’m attaching the link to my GitHub where my code is located, as well as screenshots of my error.

The error is in your first screenshot.

getTagPose(…) returns an Optional. When you call .get() against it, it’s null, so it throws an exception.

I suspect the value returned by aprilId() (a value pulled from the limelight table in NetworkTables) is not a valid AprilTag ID. Looks like that method default to 0, so it’s probably just that you don’t have a tag in view of your camera. You’ll need to handle that better.
